<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. transmit_error_response_len() sets connection->in_access_handler = true and calls MHD_queue_response(connection,...). MHD_queue_response() may call MHD_connection_handle_idle(), which in its state machine can call build_header_response(). If build_header_response() fails it invokes CONNECTION_CLOSE_ERROR (used elsewhere to invoke transmit_error_response_len), which can call transmit_error_response_len() again. That creates an indirect call chain: transmit_error_response_len -> MHD_queue_response -> MHD_connection_handle_idle -> build_header_response -> CONNECTION_CLOSE_ERROR -> transmit_error_response_len, so Rule 17.2 is violated.
</scenario>
